\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">a hint of a smile</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">There was more than a hint of sadness in his voice.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">The walls were painted white with a hint of peach.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">Gail searched his face for the slightest hint of regret.</span></li></ul><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" id=\"hint2_unbox_5\" unbox=\"extra_examples\"><span class=\"box_title\">Extra Examples</span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Do I detect a hint of jealousy in your voice?</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">He showed not a hint of remorse.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Her voice betrayed a hint of uneasiness.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">She felt the first hint of panic as the train pulled into the station.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">The slightest hint of gossip upset her.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">a dish with a strong hint of garlic</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">‘It won't take long,’ he persisted, without the slightest hint of apology.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">There was a hint of amusement in his voice.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">He vowed that no hint of scandal would ever be attached to him.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Her eyes held a hint of mockery.</span></li></ul></span></div><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" id=\"hint2_unbox_6\" unbox=\"snippet\"><span class=\"box_title\">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">adjective</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">strong</li><l